HEADWORD: CPI
<hw>CPI</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>the <er>consumer price index</er>, an
index of the cost of all goods and services to a typical consumer. The
increase of this value each year is one measure of monetary
inflation.</def> <mark>[acronym]</mark>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> consumer price index, cost-of-living
index.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

